# Force LF line endings for all text files. Without this, Git on Windows
# checks files out with CRLF (per `core.autocrlf=true`), which conflicts
# with the Prettier `endOfLine: "lf"` setting and breaks `pnpm format:check`
# locally. CI runs on Linux and is unaffected, but the local pre-push hook
# fails with 80+ false positives. This file is the standard fix.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files — never normalize
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.zip binary
